title: (x) 'Five West Country Folk Songs': old sheet music book / Can anyone identify this typeface? - University Roman {Florian}
content:
Hi there, I just found an old sheet music book and it has a lovely typeface on the cover. Anyone have any idea what it's called?

thanks, Laurie  
 [http://i136.photobucket.com/albums/q198/surfloz/oldfont.jpg](http://web.archive.org/web/20131106084249/http:/i136.photobucket.com/albums/q198/surfloz/oldfont.jpg "http://i136.photobucket.com/albums/q198/surfloz/oldfont.jpg")
author: lauriemccall

comments.content:
Hi Laurie,  
that’s [University Roman](http://web.archive.org/web/20131106084249/http:/new.myfonts.com/fonts/letraset/university-roman/?testdrive=dock%3Dfalse%26size%3D61%26w%3D600%26src%3Dcustom%26text%3DFIVE%2520WEST%2520COUNTRY%2520FOLK%2520SONGS%26fg%3D000000%26bg%3Dffffff%26goodies%3Dfit%26seed%3D33).  
There’s a special place on Typophile for such requests – I’ll move this thread to the [Type ID Board](http://web.archive.org/web/20131106084249/http:/www.typophile.com/typeid).  
F

Thank you Florian, I didn't realise that there is a seperate forum for this type of question.

Laurie
